face it the epics seem..well...dated.<br>
<br>
this is great idea not only for the warrior but epic but for all epics across the board...and would allow epics to be well different..doesnt feel very epic when the guy next to you with his &quot;epic&quot; has the same exact item does it..lol<br>
<br>
anyway i think with 3 expansions since the epics the idea of upgrading them through quests even more epic than the epic would be a great idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=guzmandivineheart>Guzman Divineheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/02 5:52:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4627.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wow</span><hr size=1> Our epic is outdated. May be they can add more steps to make the ratio up to date.<br>
But all this wont fix the real problem with our epic.<br>
To gain the full benefit from our Epic we have to &quot;sacrifice&quot; 2 slots. Basically all classes (except rangers) have a 100 HP or mana item in one slot, thats the reason why they use it much longer. We just have a 50 HP item per slot.<br>
<br>
And if they give us 2 items with stats like used in endgame, then all other classes will start to whine.<br>
<br>
Its a dead horse. Let it rott.<br>
<br>
But its a shame to see wizards, monks, magicians and a few other classes after months of VT and Tower of Sol Ro farming wearing their epic, while warriors epic are rotting in bankslots since velious (not even endgame of velious) and wait for a better time.<br>
<br>
Guzman - Overlord<br>
www.Darkwind.info <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draxusmt>Draxus MT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 9:11:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4627.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wow</span><hr size=1> I can't think of anything in Velious that I would replace my red epic with.  Even with a BoC, I would still off hand the red epic.  In fact, it wouldn't be until high end Luclin that I would finally find something to dump the red blade for. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6347">Veteran Draxus Diablus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
